modules.description: Compares two values using a custom ordering, returns the predecessor and successor of a value, and calculates the distance between two values. Works with the abstract type `t` representing ordered elements. Used to navigate and measure relationships in ordered sequences like timestamps or enumerated states.

Compares integer values and returns their relative order, computes the predecessor and successor of an integer, and calculates the absolute distance between two integers. Works exclusively with integer data types. Used in scenarios requiring ordered integer manipulation, such as range validation or sequence generation.

Provides operations to compare, find predecessors and successors, and calculate distances between elements of a type `t`. Works with ordered data types that support sequential traversal and metric comparison. Used to implement algorithms requiring ordered enumeration and distance-based logic, such as pathfinding or sequence analysis.
